Definition: lasting a very short time
Example: the ephemeral joys of childhood; a passing fancy; youth's transient beauty; love is transitory but it is eternal; fugacious blossoms
Synonyms: noun, time, ephemera, attribute, ephemeralness, ephemerality, passing, short-lived, transient, person, event, transiency, transience, transitory, transitoriness, fugacious, fugaciousness, fugacity, lasting, a, very, short, the, joys, of, childhood, fancy, youth, s, beauty, love, is, but, it, eternal, blossoms
Category: adj.all
